---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const updated = "May 13, 2026";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy · Subbun" description="How Subbun handles your data.">
  <article class="container-tight py-16 prose-doc">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      Subbun is a Chrome extension that translates Japanese video subtitles
      into English. This policy explains what data we collect, what we don't
      collect, and what we do with it.
    </p>

    <h2>What we do NOT collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Subtitle text.</strong> Translation runs entirely in your
        browser using Chrome's built-in on-device AI APIs (Gemini Nano and the
        Translator API). Subtitle content never leaves your computer.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The pages you visit or videos you watch.</strong> URLs, titles,
        video IDs, and search queries are never logged or sent.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Your account data on any streaming service.</strong> Subbun
        never reads, transmits, or stores credentials, cookies, or
        identifiers from YouTube, Netflix, Prime, or any other supported
        site.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>An anonymous instance ID.</strong> A randomly generated UUID
        created on install. We use it to validate Pro license keys against our
        license server. It is not tied to your name, email, or any account.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Your Pro license key, if you have one.</strong> Used only to
        verify your subscription is active. Provided by Lemon Squeezy (our
        merchant of record) at purchase time.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Optional anonymous usage stats.</strong> If telemetry is
        enabled (default on; opt out in the popup): aggregate counts of how
        many lines were translated, which engines succeeded, and caught
        errors with Japanese text scrubbed out. No content, no URLs, no
        identifiers.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where data goes when it goes anywhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>License server:</strong> <code>api.getsubbun.com</code>. Receives
        only your instance ID and license key during activation and periodic
        re-validation.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Payment processing:</strong> handled entirely by
        <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lemon Squeezy</a>,
        our merchant of record. We never see your card details.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Permissions</h2>
    <p>
      Subbun requests these Chrome permissions and uses them for the following:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>storage</strong> — to remember your settings and license state.</li>
      <li><strong>activeTab / scripting</strong> — to inject the translation overlay into the supported video and form sites.</li>
      <li><strong>alarms</strong> — to refresh your license check once a day.</li>
      <li><strong>offscreen</strong> — to pre-warm the on-device AI model so the first subtitle appears quickly.</li>
      <li><strong>host_permissions</strong> — limited to the supported video sites (YouTube, Netflix, Prime, Abema, Niconico, Crunchyroll, TVer, NHK Plus, U-NEXT, Disney+, Hulu Japan).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights and choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Opt out of anonymous usage stats anytime in the popup settings.</li>
      <li>Deactivate your Pro license to remove it from this device.</li>
      <li>Uninstall the extension — all local data is removed by Chrome automatically.</li>
      <li>
        Email <a href="mailto:support@getsubbun.com">support@getsubbun.com</a> to
        request deletion of any server-side records associated with your
        instance ID or license key.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      Subbun is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
      data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal
      data, contact us and we will delete it.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will
      be noted at the top of this page with a new "Last updated" date.
      Continued use of the extension after a change means you accept the
      updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or concerns? Email
      <a href="mailto:support@getsubbun.com">support@getsubbun.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
